Dialogue: 5,0:09:04.73,0:09:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,561)}I don't like playing dirty like you, Miuna.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:11.53,0:09:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Miuna!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:14.27,0:09:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.44,0:09:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I really showed 'em this time!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:16.66,0:09:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:17.51,0:09:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how they were \Nmaking a Wooden Maiden?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:20.08,0:09:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I totally trashed it!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:22.70,0:09:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Trashed it?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:24.00,0:09:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:24.64,0:09:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I drew all over it, and then \NI ripped up its clothes!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.70,0:09:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can't even tell it's a \NWooden Maiden anymore! Like, at all!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.70,0:09:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:33.34,0:09:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.42,0:09:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really playing dirty!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.30,0:09:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Miuna?!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:38.61,0:09:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate playing dirty like that!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:43.15,0:09:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Miuna!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.60,0:09:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii{-kun}, wait!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:50.05,0:09:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd you follow me?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:56.35,0:09:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An octopus.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:57.99,0:09:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, boy...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.29,0:10:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Octopuses are cowards.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:04.23,0:10:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're kind of like an octopus.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:07.25,0:10:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}you're{\i0} calling me an octopus too?!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:09.74,0:10:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? "Too"?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:11.40,0:10:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, never mind...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:12.84,0:10:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When they get scared by fish \Nthey don't know, they spit out ink.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:17.02,0:10:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, dark black stuff.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:18.59,0:10:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The ink tastes really good, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.52,0:10:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Like when it's in squid ink pasta.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:23.18,0:10:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should it be "octopus ink" pasta?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:25.24,0:10:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never made it, so—
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.72,0:10:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:28.22,0:10:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was it again?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:32.05,0:10:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, why'd you ask them to try \Nour sushi bowl in the first place?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:37.57,0:10:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:38.82,0:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You normally don't do stuff like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:41.24,0:10:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're usually hiding behind us.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.57,0:10:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:46.61,0:10:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Another octopus?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.76,0:10:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, look!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.59,0:10:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... Akari's boyfriend!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.81,0:11:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii{-kun}, the bottom's turning black!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:11.10,0:11:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.63,0:11:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't even make \Nrice porridge by yourself?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we can {just }add some \Nmiso to mask the taste{ of the scorched parts}.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:19.66,0:11:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:21.43,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:23.79,0:11:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I caused you trouble...
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.58,0:11:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:26.88,0:11:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something else you should be apologizing for, you criminal.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:29.84,0:11:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Criminal?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:31.54,0:11:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a kid, and yet you \Nput the moves on my big sister.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.68,0:11:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{I...}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:37.23,0:11:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the hell were you \Ndrowning yourself for?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.32,0:11:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to contact Akari.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.84,0:11:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't even come to the supermarket.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:44.63,0:11:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I'd go see her {directly }myself.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:47.74,0:11:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Go see her? In Shioshishio?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:50.23,0:11:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:51.77,0:11:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I borrowed some diving \Nequipment from my friend,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:54.66,0:11:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but it kept filling up with water—
Dialogue: 5,0:11:57.32,0:11:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you get off \Nplaying the {sad }victim?!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:59.49,0:12:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Stop it, Hii{-kun}!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:01.69,0:12:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a criminal! A lowlife!{"lowlife / no-good ___ / scoundrel / villain" or something else for the second}{the memory of dark_sage suggests the accredited "low-down player"}{~_~}{lol}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:04.46,0:12:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Having an affair is totally unforgivable—
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.33,0:12:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}, lemme have some spirit fire.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:21.33,0:12:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're quite the sinner, \Nwalking over the servant of a god.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:26.18,0:12:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:27.48,0:12:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I spent so much time cleaning up around here and doing things for you,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:32.79,0:12:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I still ended up miserable.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:34.73,0:12:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are you gonna \Nkeep ditching work?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:37.64,0:12:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about \Nfinding a job down here...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:40.49,0:12:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,though there aren't {really }that many options.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:42.62,0:12:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to give up on him just because his daughter didn't approve of you?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:46.89,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite being cooped up in here all the time, \Nyou sure know a lot of gossip.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.41,0:12:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only been three years \Nsince she lost her mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:57.95,0:13:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand why she \Ncan't approve of me.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:00.93,0:13:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother's name was Miori, I believe. \NAnd she lived in a house just off the rocks.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.30,0:13:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you remember her.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:06.92,0:13:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.26,0:13:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a real beauty{babe} with a sweet ass.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:13.01,0:13:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Miori{-san} had been banished, she wasn't bitter toward me.{even after miori left our village, she continued to treat me well}{as in, she wasnt bitter towards every single resident of the village for kicking her out}
